SIMPLE: retinue
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Retinue
<hw>Ret"i*nue</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>retinue</ets>, OF. <ets>retinue</ets>, fr. <ets>retenir</ets> to
retain, engage, hire. See <er>Retain</er>.]</ety> <def>The body of
retainers who follow a prince or other distinguished person; a train of
attendants; a suite.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Others of your insolent <qex>retinue</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>What followers, what <qex>retinue</qex> canst thou gain?</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To have at one's retinue</b></col>, <cd>to keep or employ
as a retainer; to retain.</cd> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Retinula</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
